It will take Tom 7 hours to dry seven pairs of socks under the same weather conditions.

Here's the reasoning:
1. Tom washed and dried 10 pairs of socks, taking a total of 10 hours (1 hour for washing and 9 hours for drying).
2. Since the weather conditions are the same, it would take the same amount of time to dry seven pairs of socks as well.
3. Therefore, Tom will need 7 hours to dry seven pairs of socks under the same weather conditions.
